The evidence with the title 'Job creation by president: number and percent ' says Oct 18, 2017  ... President Bush created 2.1 million jobs during his eight - year term.That's because he struggled with two recessions . He lost 3.6 million jobs in 2008, his last year in office . The job gains were before that, as he recovered from the 2001 recession . He responded to it with stimulus checks and the Bush tax cuts. 
